<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06206232 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06206232 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  The Marin Municipal Water District has voted to place on the November ballotan $80 million bond issue that would raise funds for the purchase of RussianRiver water. The board voted 3-2 Monday night after a public hearing in SanRafael attended by about 150 people. The plan would provide the district with10,000 additional acre-feet of water per year, increasing the district'ssupply by about 30 percent in years where rationing remains a threat.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  BOND ISSUE ON WATER OK'D FOR MARIN BALLOT  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910724  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  82  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday July 24, 199100206232,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>